Task 1 (W)
a) Why does an arrival event need to generate a new arrival event?

An arrival event must generate a new arrival event because customers continue arriving during the simulation. If no new arrival event is created, the simulation would stop after the first customer arrives. Generating the next arrival keeps the event list updated and allows the simulation to continue.

b) Which event should be generated by the start of the service (of a single service point)?

The start of the service should generate a service completion (exit) event. This event is scheduled for the future when the customer's service time ends, allowing the simulator to know when the service point becomes available again.
